detaileddescription.para: "Next Largest Power of 2 Given a binary integer value x, the next largest power of 2 can be computed by a SWAR algorithm that recursively "folds" the upper bits into the lower bits. This process yields a bit vector with the same most significant 1 as x, but all 1's below it. Adding 1 to that value yields the next largest power of 2. For a 32-bit value:"
